<item>
            <title>[FLINK-7226] REST responses contain invalid content-encoding header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7226</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5705&quot; title=&quot;webmonitor&amp;#39;s request/response use UTF-8 explicitly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5705&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5705&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; made changes to the &lt;tt&gt;RuntimeMonitorHandler&lt;/tt&gt; to set the &lt;tt&gt;content-encoding&lt;/tt&gt; header to &lt;tt&gt;UTF-8&lt;/tt&gt;. This however isn&apos;t a valid value for this header, and should instead be included in the &lt;tt&gt;content-type&lt;/tt&gt; header.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13088368">FLINK-7226</key>
